  "local_port": 40086,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Which is a suitable solar panel installation provider near San Gabriel, California CA?",
  "response": "Finding a reliable solar panel installation provider near San Gabriel, California, involves considering factors like reputation, customer reviews, certifications, pricing, and the quality of products offered. Here are some reputable companies that operate in or around the San Gabriel area:\n\n1. **Sungevity Solar**\n   - **Overview:** Sungevity is a well-known solar company that offers customized solar solutions for residential customers. They handle everything from system design to installation.\n   - **Website:** [Sungevity](https://www.sungevity.com/)\n   \n2. **SolarCity (now part of Tesla Energy)**\n   - **Overview:** SolarCity, acquired by Tesla, provides solar panel installation along with energy storage solutions like the Tesla Powerwall.\n   - **Website:** [Tesla Solar](https://www.tesla.com/energy)\n\n3. **Sunrun**\n   - **Overview:** Sunrun is one of the largest residential solar installers in the U.S., offering flexible financing options, including leases and power purchase agreements (PPAs).\n   - **Website:** [Sunrun](https://www.sunrun.com/)\n\n4. **Gardner Solar**\n   - **Overview:** Gardner Solar is a California-based company that has been providing solar solutions for over two decades, offering both sales and installation services.\n   - **Website:** [Gardner Solar](https://gardnersolar.com/)\n\n5. **Momentum Solar**\n   - **Overview:** Momentum Solar offers comprehensive solar services, including consultation, design, permitting, and installation. They are known for personalized customer service.\n   - **Website:** [Momentum Solar](https://www.momentumsolar.com/)\n\n6. **Solar Spectrum**\n   - **Overview:** Serving Southern California, Solar Spectrum provides customized solar solutions with a focus on high-quality installations and customer satisfaction.\n   - **Website:** [Solar Spectrum](https://www.solarspectrumla.com/)\n\n7. **MEP Solar & Energy**\n   - **Overview:** MEP Solar specializes in residential and commercial solar installations in the Greater Los Angeles area, including San Gabriel.\n   - **Website:** [MEP Solar](https://mepsolar.com/)\n\n**Tips for Choosing the Right Provider:**\n\n- **Check Certifications:** Look for certifications like the North American Board of Certified Energy Practitioners (NABCEP), which ensures that the installer meets industry standards.\n  \n- **Read Reviews:** Platforms like [Yelp](https://www.yelp.com/), [Google Reviews](https://www.google.com/maps), and the [Better Business Bureau (BBB)](https://www.bbb.org/) can provide insights into other customers' experiences.\n  \n- **Compare Quotes:** Obtain multiple quotes to compare pricing, financing options, and the quality of components (like solar panels and inverters).\n  \n- **Ask About Warranties:** Ensure that the provider offers strong warranties on both equipment and installation workmanship.\n  \n- **Inquire About Permitting and Incentives:** A good installer should handle the permitting process and help you take advantage of local, state, and federal incentives or rebates.\n\n**Additional Resources:**\n\n- **[EnergySage Solar Marketplace](https://www.energysage.com/):** Allows you to compare quotes from multiple solar installers in your area.\n  \n- **[California Solar Consumer Guide](https://www.cpuc.ca.gov/General.aspx?id=25284):** Provided by the California Public Utilities Commission, this guide offers information on selecting a solar provider and understanding solar contracts.\n\nBefore making a decision, it's advisable to contact a few providers to discuss your specific needs, assess your property's solar potential, and understand the financing options available to you.",
